"Wireless communication isn't magic - it's just a very complicated way to make electrons do what we want."$- Nikola Tesla (liberal interpretation, though he did predict Wi-Fi)
"In theory, radio waves are perfect. In practice, they get absorbed by that wall you forgot to account for."$- Myers' Law of Wireless Networks (empirical observation)
"What users call 'bad signal' is usually just interference, poorly placed antennas, or your neighbor running a microwave."$- Ramesh Raskar, MIT Media Lab researcher (2019 lecture on wireless tech)
